               <msContents>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_54-item1">
                     <locus>(fol. 1)</locus>
                     <author key="person_315944519">Edmund Rich</author>
                     <title key="work_1447">Speculum ecclesiae</title>
                     <rubric>Speculum Sancti Edmundi</rubric>
                     <incipit>Videte ad quid vocati estis. Ista verba apostoli</incipit>
                     <note>Preceded by a list of chapters and prologue.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_54-item2">
                     <locus>(fol. 24v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_2465074">Richard Rolle</author>
                     <title key="work_4286">Emendatio uitae</title>
                     <rubric>Libellus Ricardi heremite de Hampole de emendacione peccatoris, qui obiit anno Domini Millesimo. cccº, xlixº. apud sanctimoniales de Hampole</rubric>
                     <incipit>Ne tardes conuerti</incipit>
                     <note>With a list of chapters. </note>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>At fol. 45 follows a hymn, versicle and prayer.</note>
                        <incipit>O quam dulcis Ihesu memoria</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#theologica" n="3" xml:id="MS_Bodl_54-item3">
                     <locus>(fol. 46)</locus>
                     <title key="work_16291" type="desc">Manual of pastoral theology</title>
                     <bibl>(Bloomfield 627)</bibl>
                     <incipit type="prologue">Bene &amp; breuiter in hoc libello ex sacris Scripturis composito tanquam in speculo</incipit>
                     <incipit>Primo notantur que Christiani</incipit>
                     <note>Containing the Apostles' Creed, notes on the Sacraments, Sins, Virtues, etc. Sections 'de modo audiendi confessionem' (fol. 64v), and on the Seven Deadly Sins and their remedies (fol. 73v) may be parts of the treatise.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#auctoritates" n="4" xml:id="MS_Bodl_54-item4">
                     <locus>(fol. 110v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_281346627"><supplied>Defensor</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_1376"><supplied>Liber scintillarum</supplied></title>
                     <!--<note>Collections of passages on religious
                        subjects from the Bible and the Fathers, each catena headed by a verse from
                        the Bible: the first is De Caritate. The first rubric is 'Isodorus de diuersis
                        sentencijs'.</note>-->
                     <incipit>Petrus apostolus dixit Ante omnia ... Salomon dixit Odium suscitat iras</incipit>
                     <explicit>et ignorant, quod gigantes ibi sint et in profundis inferni convivae eius</explicit>
                     <finalRubric>Hic expliciunt Parabolae Salomonis</finalRubric>
                     <bibl>See Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> VIII/2, p. 392</bibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On fol. 155v is a character of a true priest, added in the 15th cent.</note>
                     <incipit>Sacerdos debet esse sanctus</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On the next page is a half-erased English note (late 15th cent.) concerning the year 1399.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="enm">Middle English</textLang>
                  </msItem>
